{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a6d106c5-8ece-453a-a9bc-6fe90c6ae37c","content":"Here's what you need to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.v3.runner.mtp` package (xUnit v3) **or**, if staying on xUnit v2, add `xunit.runner.mtp`:\n\n   ```xml\n   <!-- For xUnit v2 (your current version): -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"*\" />\n\n   <!-- OR migrate to xUnit v3: -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3\" Version=\"*\" />\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3.runner.mtp\" Version=\"*\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Enable MTP** in your project file:\n\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   Or run the test project directly as an executable (MTP makes test projects self-contained apps).\n\n**Key notes:**\n- `TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport` ensures `dotnet test` uses MTP instead of VSTest.\n- If you're open to upgrading to **xUnit v3**, that's the recommended path — it has native MTP support and is actively developed. However, v3 has API changes (e.g., `Xunit` namespace → `Xunit.v3`).\n- If you want to stay on xUnit **v2.9.3**, `xunit.runner.mtp` bridges v2 to MTP.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"78f9c08d-fded-4377-80cc-105909076a45","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using `xunit.runner.visualstudio`) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":479,"requestId":"0842:307F5D:811AFAF:8F41042:69EABD7B"},"id":"b08278a5-8afc-4a72-823b-d15ee108b8ae","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:47:02.121Z","parentId":"da8d8ad9-faad-4dd2-9537-95ffef23065d"}
